## 8. Implementation Priorities

### Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1-2)
1. **WorkflowError Base Class**: Create base class and migrate existing errors
2. **Error Classification**: Implement classifyWorkflowError() function
3. **Enhanced Retry**: Integrate ai-functions RetryPolicy with workflow handlers

### Phase 2: DLQ & Circuit Breaker (Week 3-4)
4. **In-Memory DLQ**: Implement DeadLetterQueue interface
5. **Circuit Breaker Integration**: Add circuit breaker support to handlers
6. **Error Hooks**: Implement onError, onRetry, onDLQ hooks

### Phase 3: Escalation Integration (Week 5-6)
7. **CascadeExecutor Enhancement**: Connect to digital-workers escalation
8. **Unified Error Flow**: End-to-end error handling with all components
9. **Documentation & Examples**: Comprehensive docs with examples

### Phase 4: Testing & Validation (Week 7-8)
10. **Error Scenario Tests**: Comprehensive test coverage
11. **Integration Tests**: Cross-package integration testing
12. **Performance Testing**: Ensure no significant overhead

---

## 9. Migration Guide

### 9.1 Backward Compatibility

All existing error classes will continue to work. New features are opt-in:

```typescript
// Existing code continues to work
const executor = new CascadeExecutor({
  tiers: { code: handler },
})

// New error handling is opt-in
const enhancedExecutor = new CascadeExecutor({
  tiers: { code: handler },
  retry: { maxRetries: 5 },
  escalation: { enabled: true },
  dlq: createInMemoryDLQ(),
})
```

### 9.2 Deprecation Path

No immediate deprecations. Future consideration:
- After ai-errors package is created, errors will be re-exported from there
- Add deprecation warnings pointing to ai-errors imports

---

## 10. Success Criteria

1. **All existing tests pass** - No breaking changes
2. **Error classification accuracy >95%** - Correct retry/escalate decisions
3. **DLQ prevents data loss** - Failed events recoverable
4. **Circuit breaker prevents cascade failures** - System stability under load
5. **Full observability** - Errors traceable end-to-end via correlationId
6. **Documentation complete** - Examples for all error handling patterns

---

